\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The University of Cape Town \'28UCT\'29 is a public higher education institution that has programmes that are accredited by the CHE.\line \line The Institution is currently applying for the accreditation of a Master of Laws in the Law of Mineral and Petroleum Extraction and Use programme that will be offered in the contact mode of delivery at the Rondebosch\'2C Main Campus.\line \line The Institution is accredited to offer the following programmes\'3A\line - Master of Laws in Marine and Environmental Law\line - Master of Laws in Environmental Law\line - Master of Laws in Private Law and Human Rights \line - Master of Laws in Intellectual Property Law\line - Master of Laws in Labour Law\line - Master of Laws in Dispute Resolution\line - Master of Laws in Commercial Law\line - Master of Laws in International Trade Law\line - Master of Laws in Shipping Law\line - Master of Laws in Tax Law\line \cell \pard 

